Viet Son,<br><br>
I would be honored to hear your stories.<br><br>
We are all connected by the events of the Vietnam War, events that still exert their influence and make us what we are today, maybe a little for the worse, but hopefully much for the better if we can listen as well as we can feel.<br><br>
You will not find more understanding and compassionate listeners than those here. Tom, Doc Del, and Tanker, are honest people.<br><br>
About labels, being called names, in my story, a small part of it lies in dealing with the label of &quot;baby killer&quot; bestowed upon me at my return from Vietnam in 1970. I could not then and still cannot shrug it off as others can. It haunts me. Intellectually, I know I was not. Emotionally, well, that's a different and complicated matter.<br><br>
Viet Son, many of us are really all in the same situation, with some variations, because we are all human beings, after all, at heart. 
